review_blob: Medium foam,  great dark rich color, slightly heavy taste,  politely bitter.  One of the best Brown Ales Ive tried yet.

Pours with a nice foamy head.  Very dark rich amber color.  Not much aroma after pouring.
Flavor gets better with each sip.  I feel its to be enjoyed slowly with a good pretzel. Ive had other Guinness but this is my first Extra Stout.
Heavier than Corona overall.  produces a good head of foam.  Nice color.  slightly bitter after  taste.  Id but it in the ice bucket at a party to give my guests variety.
stinky  aroma.  awfull  taste.  had to wash my mouth out after tasting.  poured  most of the  bottle out.
Darker color more like a dark beer.  Aroma was like a soft fruit drink.  seemed sweet in taste but not fruity.  it is a fair brew but not worth the price.
bottled.  kind of a light golden color with a light oaky aroma.  texture is heavier than Am used to but acceptable. taste was slightly bitter.
